      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">29/7/82 ¶  ¶ I have owed you a letter for a long time, dear Mr Holtze; but as you are in communication with Professor Tate, ¶ Tate had visited Maurice Holtze earlier in the year when he accompanied a ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">82.07.29</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Maurice Holtze</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">GRG 19/391, State Records of South Australia, Adelaide.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">29/7/82</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Seit langer Zeit schuldige ich Ihnen einen Brief, lieber Herr Holtze; aber da Sie mit Hr. Prof. Tate in Verbindung sind, wird er Ihnen über die neuen Pflanzen wohl geschrieben haben, welche er entdeckte. Es sind nicht viele, aber es ist Einiges von hohem Interesse darunter. Ich bearbeite dieselben jezt. Wie Sie aus beigefügtem Blatte ersehen werden, hat auch Mr Alfred Giles in Ihrer<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Nähe</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>eine neue Bauhinia (mit ungetheilten Blättern) gefunden, welche mir durch Mr Bailey zuging; wir haben diese merkwürdige Pflanze noch aus keiner anderen Sammlung, auch fehlen noch die Früchte.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es müssen bei Ihnen noch manche andere Pflanzen vorkommen, welche bisher unbeschrieben sind, u. ich würde Ihnen rathen mit jeder Post ein kleines Packet zu senden.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Von den dortigen Nymphaea-Arten, auch von der niedlichen Sumpf Pflanze Monochoria cyanea mit blauer Blumen Ähre hätte ich gern Samen in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Thon geknetet</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>und dann langsam getrocknet. Bei diesem Sammeln in Ihren Lagunen bitte ich auch auf solche Wasser Pflanzen zu achten, welche keine schön aussehenden Blüthen haben. Eben unter den kleinen und unscheinbaren Pflanzen giebt es am meisten<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Neues</hi>
               </seg>, und<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">solche</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sind ja so leicht zu trocknen. Ich sende Ihnen einen Probebogen eines neuen Werkes, welches eben unter der Presse ist; wahrscheinlich wird der erste Band am Ende dieses Jahres erscheinen u. soll Ihnen dann gesandt werden.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.9861in; text-indent: 0.493in; "
               xml:lang="de">Mit bestem Grusse<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Ich hätte gern eine neue Pflanze nach Ihnen genannt, es bedarf aber des Completirens Ihres Materials neuer Arten, wie früher schon geschrieben.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">29/7/82</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have owed you a letter for a long time, dear Mr Holtze; but as you are in communication with Professor Tate,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Tate had visited Maurice Holtze earlier in the year when he accompanied a parliamentary party investigating the potentialities of the Northern Territory; see M. Holtze to M, 21 May 1882.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he will probably have written to you about the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>new plants he discovered. There are not very many, but there are some of great interest among them. I am working on them just now.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M described<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Strobilanthes Tatei</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in B82.12.05 and (with Tate)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Pachynema sphenandrum</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in B82.14.01, both collected by Tate in Arnhem Land, NT. M also erected a new genus,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Tatea</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in B83.04.07, on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the basis of another Tate collection in Arnhem Land.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>As you will see from the enclosed sheet,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sheet not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mr Alfred Giles, too, discovered<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">vicinity</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a new<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Bauhinia</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(with undivided leaves)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>came to me through Mr Bailey. We do not have this remarkable plant from any other collection, and the fruits are still lacking.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There must be many other plants occurring in your area that so far are<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>undescribed, and I should advise you to send a small parcel with each mail.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Of the local<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Nymphaea</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>species there, also of the pretty swamp plant<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Monochoria cyanea</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with the blue flower spike, I should like to have seeds<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">kneaded into clay</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and then slowly dried. While collecting in your waterholes I also ask you to look out for those aquatic plants that do not have beautiful-looking flowers. Particularly among such small and insignificant plants will be found most that is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">new</hi>
               </seg>, and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">these</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>are also so easy to dry. I also am sending you a proof sheet of a new work that is presently in press; the first volume will probably be published at the end of this year and will then be sent to you.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Proof sheet not found.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>It would have been a sheet<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Systematic c</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">ensus</seg>, dated 1882 on its title page, but issued as B83.03.04.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Printing was underway by April (M to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>A. de Candolle, 9 April 1882) and had reached sheet<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by August (M to R. Tate, 22 August 1882<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 82-08-22c)).The planned second volume on the Evasculares was never published.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With best greetings</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I should like to have named a new plant after you, but it requires the completing of your material of new plants, as I have already previously written.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See, for example,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>item 160 in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M. Holtze, 1881<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 81-00-00j).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Bauhinia</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Monochoria cyanea</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Nymphaea</p>
         </div>
      </body>
